The course provides students with basic knowledge about the main concepts of information law and ethics, including privacy protection and data protection principles, as these affect the everyday practices of organisations and individuals. The course comprises lectures and seminars, and concludes with a written group work task the topic for which is agreed during the course.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The objective of the course is to provide an overview of current topics of information law and introduce certain dilemmas related to information law that can arise in the work of organisations and in people's everyday lives. The course also provides an overview of current principles of data protection, freedom of expression and its limits, public information and information ethics.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  .Upon the completion of the course, the student: *	knows main theories of information law and ethics; *	is able to recognise and express the dilemmas concerning the information processing and is prepared to analyse daily practices in information processing from the point of view of values and principles; *	has an overview of the principles of data protection, freedom of expression and public information.
